                            <comment id="13204704" author="robrosko" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2012 18:10:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;quickstart&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13207815" author="robrosko" created="Tue, 14 Feb 2012 16:37:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Unmounting the login page (comment out mountPage(&quot;/user/login&quot;, LoginPage.class) in WicketApplication) seems to solve the issue as a workaround. Though, the nice mount is gone and you have to use: &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8080/login/wicket/bookmarkable/de.rob.login.LoginPage&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8080/login/wicket/bookmarkable/de.rob.login.LoginPage&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This seems to back the theory of a broken MountedMapper (or related code).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13211965" author="mgrigorov" created="Mon, 20 Feb 2012 16:32:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think it is related to how Tomcat&apos;s handles urls which end with &apos;..&apos;.&lt;br/&gt;
This patch appends &apos;/&apos; if the url ends with &apos;..&apos; and seems to solve the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13211989" author="robrosko" created="Mon, 20 Feb 2012 17:21:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tested the patch and can confirm that it works for me, too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13213765" author="mgrigorov" created="Wed, 22 Feb 2012 17:07:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is another patch which I believe is better.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13214866" author="bumer" created="Thu, 23 Feb 2012 17:20:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m using Jetty 6.1.26 and had the same issue. Patch works for me also.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
